WEBVTT

00:00.875 --> 00:03.878
♪♪

00:22.397 --> 00:24.524
-Morning.
-Hi.

00:24.524 --> 00:29.279
-Here's my 49 on Liery.
-How thorough
is that, Diane?

00:29.279 --> 00:33.616
It's the version you can
take the kids to. Why?
Who you lookin' to hurt?

00:33.616 --> 00:39.330
Diane, Jimmy Liery died
at the hands of a crook
and a killer like he was.

00:39.330 --> 00:42.000
From my point of view,
that's the end of the story.

00:42.000 --> 00:46.421
I'm sorry that it
caused complications in your
personal life. You told me...

00:46.421 --> 00:48.131
that your relationship
with Bobby was at
a difficult point.

00:48.131 --> 00:50.592
I was wrong to think
we could steer around that.

00:55.180 --> 00:58.058
I wanna get
to work.

00:58.058 --> 01:00.852
Any permanent damage?
Not from this.

01:01.811 --> 01:05.106
-Take care, Diane.
-Hmm.

01:20.163 --> 01:22.916
-Mornin'.
-Oh, hi, Bobby.

01:22.916 --> 01:25.001
-Andy.
-Hey.

01:25.001 --> 01:27.587
-Boss change the chart?
-No. I'm off.

01:27.587 --> 01:30.965
-Um, I wanted to talk
to you about dinner.
-What's up?

01:30.965 --> 01:34.385
Uh, if we had to, would it
be okay eatin' at my place
instead of goin' out?

01:34.385 --> 01:35.762
Sure.

01:35.762 --> 01:38.890
My ex-husband is
bein' a jerk about whether
he'll take the boys.

01:38.890 --> 01:42.727
-You don't have to talk me
into home cookin'.
-Well, the alternative is...

01:42.727 --> 01:44.479
-we could do it
another night.
-No, no.

01:44.479 --> 01:48.108
-This is--This is good.
-Okay. I'll see you later.

01:48.108 --> 01:51.152
Yeah.
We shoot for,
like, 7:00.

01:51.152 --> 01:53.446
Yeah.
Just, uh, give me a call,
and let me know.

01:55.073 --> 01:57.158
-Hi, Diane.
-Hi.

01:59.119 --> 02:01.204
-Morning.
-How's it goin'?

02:05.959 --> 02:07.252
(sighs)

02:07.252 --> 02:11.047
Give me a heads-up
when it's gonna come to shots.
I'll make for the fish tank.

02:12.006 --> 02:15.009
♪♪

03:18.198 --> 03:19.616
♪♪

03:36.007 --> 03:37.592
We need to talk
to a detective.

03:37.592 --> 03:40.720
-I'm Detective Simone.
This is Detective Sipowicz.
-How's it goin'?

03:40.720 --> 03:44.098
Mr. Kozler and I
are diamond dealers.
I'm Jerry Silverton.

03:44.098 --> 03:47.852
His sister is missing with
a million, four in stones.

03:47.852 --> 03:51.397
-Well, let's talk in here.
-All right. That's fine.
Thank you.

03:51.397 --> 03:54.025
Right this way.

03:54.025 --> 03:56.236
How long has your sister
been missing?

03:56.236 --> 03:58.321
I last heard from Alice
two days ago.

03:58.321 --> 04:00.949
Day following
my consigning the stones.

04:00.949 --> 04:04.577
Your sister give any indication
she was worried, felt like
she was in danger?

04:04.577 --> 04:08.456
-No.
-Consigning diamonds--you've
done that with her in the past?

04:08.456 --> 04:12.085
I've been doing business
with her brother for 15 years.
This was my favor to him.

04:12.085 --> 04:15.797
Uh, we both agree,
the person responsible
for this is Fred Morgan.

04:15.797 --> 04:19.592
My sister's been seeing him,
and he told Alice
he had a buyer.

04:19.592 --> 04:24.013
Yesterday, he contacted
a dealer at the diamond exchange
up 47th Street who's a friend.

04:24.013 --> 04:27.600
Offered to sell
exactly what I consigned.
They're meeting at 10:00.

04:27.600 --> 04:30.395
If those are Hy's diamonds,
something terrible
has happened to Alice...

04:30.395 --> 04:33.898
-because she wouldn't stand by.
She's honorable.
-Know what Morgan looks like?

04:33.898 --> 04:37.694
-Could you point him out to us?
-Yes. I can.
I've seen him several times.

04:39.737 --> 04:41.614
Tell her we're thinkin' of her.

04:44.242 --> 04:48.579
-You guys got a minute?
Gina's at the Bellevue E.R.
-Our Gina?

04:48.579 --> 04:51.582
-Yeah. She got attacked
on the street.
-What happened to her?

04:51.582 --> 04:56.212
The cop said the E.R. doc told
him her life's not in danger.
She was slashed with a knife.

04:56.212 --> 04:59.173
-Oh, my God.
-Yeah. There were no witnesses
at the scene.

04:59.173 --> 05:03.261
Evidently, he dragged her
into a vacant building. Take
Diane. Get Gina's statement.

05:03.261 --> 05:06.139
-Yeah. Sure, boss.
-All right.

05:06.139 --> 05:08.641
Lieu, uh, these two guys--
the taller one's sister
is missing...

05:08.641 --> 05:11.561
with a jewelry consignment,
belongs to the other one.

05:11.561 --> 05:14.814
Now both 'em like a guy for
takin' her off, maybe hurting
her. They set up a meetin'...

05:14.814 --> 05:17.358
-in the diamond district
in about a half an hour.
-Yeah. All right.

05:17.358 --> 05:21.779
-What's that?
-Gina the P.A.A.--
she got attacked and slashed.

05:21.779 --> 05:23.740
-Oh, man. It serious?
-She all right?

05:23.740 --> 05:26.242
I don't know.
If you're going to do it,
you ought to get going.

05:26.242 --> 05:28.870
Sure.

05:28.870 --> 05:32.081
That's probably
the last scheduling advice
we're gonna need from you.

05:33.082 --> 05:35.335
♪♪

05:42.842 --> 05:44.385
She hasn't been stitched.

05:44.385 --> 05:46.554
-Resident wanted to wait for
the plastic surgeon.
-Okay.

05:46.554 --> 05:48.556
-Brought you some visitors.
MEDAVOY: Hey, Gina.

05:48.556 --> 05:52.060
RUSSELL:
How are you, Gina?
-A man attacked me.

05:52.060 --> 05:56.147
He tried to rape me,
but I didn't let him.
He cut me with a knife.

05:56.147 --> 05:59.317
-That's why they want
a specialist to stitch on me.
-You're gonna be fine, Gina.

05:59.317 --> 06:01.527
Do you remember
what he looked like?

06:01.527 --> 06:05.907
He was a--
a big, strong white guy.
He must have been following me.

06:05.907 --> 06:08.451
He... grabbed me,

06:08.451 --> 06:12.538
and he dragged me into
this empty building, and
he started trying to rape me.

06:12.538 --> 06:16.167
I was hitting him,
and he had this knife,
and he said...

06:16.167 --> 06:20.171
that if I didn't stop
and let him do it,
that he was gonna stab me.

06:20.171 --> 06:24.926
But I couldn't stop,
and he started cutting on me.

06:24.926 --> 06:29.389
And I kept hitting him
and screaming, and--
and finally he ran out.

06:29.389 --> 06:31.557
-Beat this guy's head in.
-Uh, could you
give us, uh,

06:31.557 --> 06:34.060
a little more
of a description,
Gina?

06:34.060 --> 06:38.606
-Uh, you said
he was tall, white.
-H-He had bad liquor breath.

06:38.606 --> 06:40.942
He looked at me
like he hated me.

06:40.942 --> 06:44.112
Huh. Anything
about his clothes?

06:44.112 --> 06:48.408
Uh, he had a--a blue jacket,
I think, a-and a blue wool cap
pulled down over his head.

06:48.408 --> 06:51.369
-You'd recognize him
if you saw him again.
-I-I don't wanna see him.

06:51.369 --> 06:55.873
-I need to spend some time
with Gina now.
-Yeah. Sure, Doc.

06:55.873 --> 06:59.085
-We'll be back to see you soon.
-Doctors are gonna
take good care of ya.

07:02.797 --> 07:06.634
That son of a bitch. She never
hurt a soul. I get my hands on
him, he's done. He's finished.

07:06.634 --> 07:08.428
James, you wanna get
yourself off the case?

07:08.428 --> 07:10.054
Hell no. I wanna
catch this guy.

07:10.054 --> 07:13.474
Then get a hold of
yourself. You keep talkin'
like that, you're off.

07:13.474 --> 07:16.269
Okay. Okay. I'll watch it,
all right? Just don't let
the boss take me off this.

07:16.269 --> 07:20.022
I-I got a hold of myself,
all right? It's straightened
out. Don't worry. I'm fine.

07:25.319 --> 07:27.488
♪♪

07:40.960 --> 07:42.753
(tapping)

07:49.302 --> 07:52.221
-Mornin', Gabe.
-What's goin' on, Jerry?

07:52.221 --> 07:55.933
New York City Detectives.
We understand you have a meeting
this morning with a Fred Morgan.

07:55.933 --> 07:58.853
Yeah. He should
be here any minute.
Is somethin' wrong?

07:58.853 --> 08:01.689
-We need to talk to him.
-Well, what did he do?
Jerry, what's goin' on here?

08:01.689 --> 08:04.525
We have some questions
that we have to put
to Mr. Morgan.

08:04.525 --> 08:07.445
Now we're gonna be
standin' right over here.
Now when he comes in,

08:07.445 --> 08:10.615
just try to act normal,
then step aside when
we move in to talk to him.

08:10.615 --> 08:13.743
-Look. Look, it's him.
-(shouts)
Where's my sister?

08:13.743 --> 08:16.704
-Where is she,
you son of a bitch?
SIMONE: Unlock the door!

08:18.664 --> 08:20.833
SIMONE:
Hey. Hey. Hey!

08:22.251 --> 08:23.669
Police! Stop!

08:26.422 --> 08:28.424
Out the way! Out the way!
Move out the way!

08:28.966 --> 08:32.762
Hey! Stop right there.
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

08:32.762 --> 08:36.349
-"Robert, Frank, David, 960."
SIPOWICZ: (panting)
Oh, that's great.

08:36.349 --> 08:40.937
RFD-960. All right? RFD-960.
15th Squad to Central.
15th Squad to Central. Okay?

08:40.937 --> 08:45.441
-Forget about it, Bobby.
-Well, what possessed you to
do that, Mr. Silverton? Idiot!

08:45.441 --> 08:49.237
-Huh?
SILVERTON:
I lost control of myself.

08:53.115 --> 08:54.909
♪♪

09:04.544 --> 09:05.920
How'd you do?

09:05.920 --> 09:09.048
Missing woman's brother
spooked the guy.
Got away in a car.

09:09.048 --> 09:13.511
-You get the plate?
-Yeah. It's registered
to an "Arthur... Boyd."

09:13.511 --> 09:15.680
-Lives here
in the precinct.
-Boyd's on his way in.

09:15.680 --> 09:18.474
The guy involved
with the sister--
this, uh, Fred Morgan--

09:18.474 --> 09:21.394
B.C.I. shows him
takin' two collars
for grand larceny.

09:21.394 --> 09:24.272
A half-assed con man.
Most recent address,
Long Island.

09:24.272 --> 09:27.942
Best case on the missing girl:
she's holed up waitin' for
Morgan. Otherwise, she's dead.

09:27.942 --> 09:31.237
Yeah, this is probably Boyd--
guy who owns the getaway car.

09:35.908 --> 09:38.286
-Mr. Boyd?
-What do you want with me?

09:38.286 --> 09:40.913
Come here. Take a seat.

09:42.373 --> 09:44.208
-Where were you
this morning?
-Out.

09:44.208 --> 09:46.335
-Yeah? Out?
-Out where?

09:46.335 --> 09:48.379
Drivin' with a friend of mine.

09:48.379 --> 09:51.924
-Who's your friend?
-Fred Morgan.

09:51.924 --> 09:53.551
Where'd you and Fred go?

09:53.551 --> 09:56.679
-Just got some breakfast,
then home.
-(chuckles)

09:56.679 --> 10:00.766
Well, Mr. Boyd, we got
a lot of witnesses that put
you and Fred somewheres else.

10:00.766 --> 10:02.768
-They're wrong.
-Hmm.
They're all wrong.

10:02.768 --> 10:05.438
Mr. Boyd,
your right move here...

10:05.438 --> 10:09.692
is to tell us what you and Fred
Morgan were doin' this morning
and where we can find Fred now.

10:09.692 --> 10:12.069
Otherwise, you are in
the way of a freight train,
you understand?

10:12.069 --> 10:14.614
-You can be an accomplice to
a grand larceny, maybe worse.
-Wait.

10:14.614 --> 10:17.033
Whoa. Whoa.
Fred was doin'
legitimate business.

10:17.033 --> 10:19.410
-What kinda business?
-S-Some diamond thing.

10:19.410 --> 10:22.413
H-He's been workin' on
this deal for the last month.
As far as I know, it's legit.

10:22.413 --> 10:25.791
Right and he was runnin'
from the cops this morning
in the diamond district,

10:25.791 --> 10:29.629
and he hopped into your car,
and with the door open
you lay 50 feet of rubber--

10:29.629 --> 10:32.798
that's you knowin'
how legitimate
this whole thing was?

10:32.798 --> 10:36.552
I-I didn't know it was the cops.
He said someone was tryin'
to rip him off.

10:36.552 --> 10:39.889
-I swear. I'm not his partner,
and I wasn't his wheel man.
-Who's he workin' with now?

10:39.889 --> 10:42.308
-His girlfriend, Alice.
-And where's she at?

10:42.308 --> 10:46.103
-She bailed out. He said
they weren't gettin' along.
-When's the last you saw her?

10:46.103 --> 10:48.314
-Last week.
-Where's Fred now?

10:48.314 --> 10:50.900
He hopped out
at a stop light.
I swear.

10:50.900 --> 10:55.529
Art, tell us where
to find him, okay? Because
if he gets away, you go to jail.

10:55.529 --> 10:58.949
Look. He's got an apartment
on Ludlow. I-I can't help
you with the girl,

10:58.949 --> 11:01.410
but if he's got
those diamonds stashed,
I could show you where.

11:01.410 --> 11:04.288
-He's got a stash
in his apartment?
-I helped him to put it there.

11:04.288 --> 11:07.458
He said it was for bein'
in the diamond business.

11:07.458 --> 11:10.670
I'm gonna call
the D.A.'s office,
try to get a warrant.

11:10.670 --> 11:14.006
If you got to know Fred,
h-he's--he's got
a good heart.

11:14.006 --> 11:16.550
Oh, I can't wait
to meet him.

11:17.176 --> 11:19.178
♪♪

11:34.610 --> 11:37.822
-I don't feel nothin' in there.
-Yeah, well, maybe something may
have fallen behind the wall?

11:37.822 --> 11:41.534
No. We--W-We knocked
a hole from inside
where this closet was...

11:41.534 --> 11:43.744
and--and fixed a ledge,
then we sealed the hole.

11:43.744 --> 11:47.498
But he must have sealed up
this closet altogether.
There was a closet here?

11:47.498 --> 11:49.125
-(hollow knocking)
-Was when I
worked on it.

11:52.002 --> 11:56.173
-You got a hammer
and flashlight?
-We'll move this thing.

11:56.173 --> 11:59.260
-Okay.
-Come over here.

12:09.603 --> 12:12.189
MAN:
Hey, what are ya doin'?
-Shut up.

12:23.075 --> 12:24.577
What the hell is that?

12:24.577 --> 12:27.455
Pull it the way
over there.
Sh--

12:30.374 --> 12:31.667
Oh, my God.

12:32.001 --> 12:35.212
-(sighs)
-Oh, my God.

12:35.212 --> 12:38.841
This bastard--
he really had to work
to get her in there.

12:38.841 --> 12:40.760
Yeah. Your friend's
got a real good heart.

12:49.059 --> 12:51.479
♪♪

12:57.860 --> 13:00.988
Lieu, this is written up,
"attempted purse-snatch,"

13:00.988 --> 13:03.324
but the description fits
what Gina gave us:
"white male,

13:03.324 --> 13:05.576
20s, medium build,
three weeks ago."

13:05.576 --> 13:07.453
-Where?
-200 block
of Third Street.

13:07.453 --> 13:10.831
Good. That's close enough.
We oughta check that out.
Okay?

13:13.334 --> 13:14.251
Yeah.

13:20.883 --> 13:24.678
So the M.E.'s early call
is that the woman was
strangled 48 hours ago.

13:24.678 --> 13:29.517
He put her in that closet,
probably thought she wouldn't
be found for 20 years.

13:29.517 --> 13:33.103
-And that was under the couch?
-Hmm. Still in the recorder,

13:33.103 --> 13:36.440
plus he had a miniature mike
taped to the inside
of one of the couch legs.

13:40.236 --> 13:43.239
<i>MAN: My buyer's</i>
<i>having trouble with the money</i>
<i>transfer. Your consignor...</i>

13:43.239 --> 13:45.658
<i>gets paid 10 times faster</i>
<i>if I go to him with the stones.</i>

13:45.658 --> 13:48.285
WOMAN:
<i>I don't like goin'</i>
<i>against my word.</i>

13:48.285 --> 13:51.580
MAN: <i>I get so depressed</i>
<i>when you doubt me like this.</i>
<i>This is what does it.</i>

13:51.580 --> 13:53.707
WOMAN:
<i>I just want everything</i>
<i>to go right.</i>

13:53.707 --> 13:56.001
<i>Well, then state the stones</i>
<i>are consigned to me...</i>

13:56.001 --> 13:59.088
<i>till I can work this out--</i>
<i>to reaffirm you have</i>
<i>faith in me.</i>

13:59.088 --> 14:03.133
<i>Let a little time go by,</i>
<i>then state it, then</i>
<i>I'm gonna kiss you.</i>

14:03.133 --> 14:06.679
WOMAN:<i> (giggles)</i>
<i>I consign these stones</i>
<i>freely to Fred Morgan.</i>

14:06.679 --> 14:08.973
<i>-Of your own free will.</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

14:08.973 --> 14:11.851
SIPOWICZ:
About a minute later,
he croaks her.

14:11.851 --> 14:15.062
-Anything on Morgan's
last address?
-He lived at his mother's house.

14:15.062 --> 14:18.482
Neighbor said that, uh,
she's been at her sister's
in Philadelphia.

14:18.482 --> 14:22.152
She's due back this afternoon.
We left a message
for the mother to come in.

14:22.152 --> 14:25.197
-Has the girlfriend's brother
been notified?
-Comin' in from Staten Island.

14:25.197 --> 14:27.867
Have him identify
the voices. And lean on
the perp's mother...

14:27.867 --> 14:29.910
-for where we can
look for this asshole.
-Yeah.

14:36.250 --> 14:38.878
RUSSELL:
All right.

14:38.878 --> 14:42.089
Excuse me.
I'm a detective.

14:42.089 --> 14:44.425
RUSSELL:
Excuse me.
I'm a detective.

14:44.425 --> 14:47.511
There was an incident, took
place about three weeks ago,
across the street.

14:47.511 --> 14:50.306
-Happen to see anything?
-No.
I didn't see anything.

14:50.306 --> 14:53.434
-What was it--a robbery
or a killing or something?
-More like an assault.

14:53.434 --> 14:56.937
No, no. But I'm not surprised
though, 'cause a bad crowd
has moved in the neighborhood.

14:56.937 --> 14:59.815
There was two men beating
a fellow right down there on
the corner just the other day.

14:59.815 --> 15:03.235
They was all drunk. And--
And--And before that,
there was, uh, some man...

15:03.235 --> 15:05.946
wrestling around
with a woman across
the street over there.

15:05.946 --> 15:08.449
-Yeah? How long ago was that?
-Oh, couple weeks or so.

15:08.449 --> 15:11.660
-Can you describe
what they looked like?
-Uh, it was a--

15:11.660 --> 15:14.705
uh, a young, um--
a white woman.

15:14.705 --> 15:18.042
She had black hair.
The man, he was white too
and kinda bulky looking,

15:18.042 --> 15:20.920
and, uh, he had
one of those, uh,
blue knit caps on.

15:20.920 --> 15:24.465
-Right.
-He had gotten a hold of her and
was dragging her, and then...

15:24.465 --> 15:26.967
two men came
and chased him away.

15:26.967 --> 15:30.179
-Can you describe more
what he looked like? Uh--
-He was just a big nothing.

15:30.179 --> 15:33.223
I'd seen him before.
I think he lives right
across the street there.

15:33.223 --> 15:35.684
-He lives
across the street?
-Yeah, I think so, in that--

15:35.684 --> 15:39.355
I-I've seen him go in
that building there--the one
with all the trash out front.

15:39.355 --> 15:42.441
-All right. Greg!
-All right. Thanks.

15:42.441 --> 15:45.653
-Can I have your name?
-My name's Margaret McClurg,
and I live right here.

15:45.653 --> 15:48.739
Okay. Thank you.
You've been very helpful.

15:48.739 --> 15:49.990
-Okay.
-Thanks.

15:49.990 --> 15:51.158
What's up?

15:51.158 --> 15:53.744
Got a location
on a suspect
across the street.

15:53.744 --> 15:56.997
Yeah?
I don't know what to do
with you, James.

15:56.997 --> 15:59.708
I'll just be backup.
I'll be okay.

16:07.925 --> 16:11.553
-What?
You Jehovah's Witness?
-No. Police.

16:11.553 --> 16:13.889
There a young white guy
living in this building--

16:13.889 --> 16:16.850
in his 20s, medium build,
wears a blue navy watch cap?

16:16.850 --> 16:19.979
Yeah. And I hope you arrest him.
He's a hoodlum.

16:19.979 --> 16:23.816
-Why do you say that, sir?
-He's got no business here.

16:23.816 --> 16:26.860
That apartment there
is vacant, unoccupied.

16:26.860 --> 16:30.990
He broke into
an empty apartment,
and he's living there.

16:30.990 --> 16:35.661
He said, if I go to the police,
he'll break my neck
and kill Eddie.

16:35.661 --> 16:38.956
-Who's Eddie?
-My little buddy.

16:41.083 --> 16:44.461
-He's not in there now?
-No. I saw him go out.

16:44.461 --> 16:47.589
I wouldn't be here
talkin' to you,
if he was in there.

16:47.589 --> 16:51.385
-All right. Thank you very much
for all your help, sir.
-Don't say I told you anything.

16:51.385 --> 16:53.846
No. We won't.
Thank you.

16:58.851 --> 17:01.145
