35:01.766 --> 35:06.395
-He's writing it up.
Boy, Andy's scary.
-Yeah.

35:06.395 --> 35:09.857
But it seems like he's able
to control it, like, down
to a 10th of a degree.

35:09.857 --> 35:12.610
That's how you wanna do it.

35:12.610 --> 35:16.072
Oh.
Talk to me like I'm a stranger.
I like that.

35:20.660 --> 35:22.620
So have a good dinner.

35:26.874 --> 35:28.751
(sighs)

35:28.751 --> 35:32.964
You want me waitin' at my crib
until you decide to come over
for another soul-search, Diane?

35:34.590 --> 35:36.551
I did that the last 10 days.

35:39.053 --> 35:41.764
Now how many ways you think
it's right to play this?

35:43.558 --> 35:45.268
I'm not playin'.

35:49.981 --> 35:52.483
I'll talk to you
tomorrow, hmm?

36:06.455 --> 36:08.457
♪♪

36:14.046 --> 36:16.465
(knocks)
I'm back.

36:16.465 --> 36:18.843
-Who beeped?
-Oh, that was Greg.

36:18.843 --> 36:22.972
Gina, that, uh, guy
you I.D.'d off the Polaroid?
He confessed.

36:22.972 --> 36:27.143
-So you don't have to worry
about bein' in contact with him.
-That's a big relief.

36:27.143 --> 36:30.062
Yeah.

36:30.062 --> 36:34.150
The doctor stopped
while you were gone. Says
he's reasonably optimistic.

36:34.150 --> 36:35.735
So that's great.

36:36.986 --> 36:42.575
I'm afraid he's...
avoiding the truth--afraid
no one'll have to do with me.

36:42.575 --> 36:46.120
-You put that outta your mind.
-That's my fear.

36:46.120 --> 36:49.123
Listen to me. You know
what we have to do?
I got hurt.

36:49.123 --> 36:52.835
-I was reluctant to call
my parents, same like you.
-They're afraid of hospitals.

36:52.835 --> 36:55.379
See, but you gotta trust
your parents to show
their love for you.

36:55.379 --> 36:58.591
They love their daughter
more than they're afraid.

36:58.591 --> 37:01.093
Afraid if they'll be upset.

37:01.093 --> 37:04.680
-I don't wanna call
till morning.
-Sure. That's fine.

37:07.892 --> 37:11.145
-You don't have to stay, James.
-I want to. Really.

37:11.145 --> 37:13.356
-It's not necessary.
-It's all right. Really.

37:21.322 --> 37:23.449
♪♪

37:26.577 --> 37:31.165
So you just took
the short course on how
my ex-husband operates.

37:31.165 --> 37:36.128
Even bein' nice,
he's gotta try and
make you cry beforehand.

37:36.128 --> 37:39.757
You mean, like not sayin'
yes about your boys
until right to the end.

37:39.757 --> 37:40.800
Yeah.

37:43.427 --> 37:46.889
-I'm glad that skell, attacked
Gina, gave ya a statement.
-Yeah.

37:46.889 --> 37:49.642
-Do they know how bad
it's gonna be?
-No. Not yet.

37:49.642 --> 37:51.894
-She got family with her?
-I'm not sure.

37:51.894 --> 37:54.480
James Martinez
is over seein' her.

37:54.480 --> 37:57.275
I could tell they had
a little something goin' on.

37:57.275 --> 38:00.611
-Oh, you pick up on
that kinda stuff, huh?
-Yeah.

38:00.611 --> 38:05.658
I do.
What'd you work today?

38:05.658 --> 38:08.244
-Um, homicide
off a jewelry theft.
-Oh.

38:08.244 --> 38:10.496
-Perp went and hung himself.
-Hmm.

38:10.496 --> 38:13.791
-They should popularize that
as an alternative to trial.
-(chuckles)

38:16.794 --> 38:18.504
This is sure fun.

38:18.504 --> 38:19.630
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

38:19.630 --> 38:24.427
I mean, dating is so hard--
just gettin' it organized.

38:24.427 --> 38:29.140
And then, uh, the guy almost
always turns out to be a jerk.

38:29.140 --> 38:33.728
But I don't wanna quit.
I'm a... big romantic.

38:33.728 --> 38:35.688
Well, you know,
that's good,

38:36.731 --> 38:39.984
-I mean, that you still
got that goin' on.
-Yeah.

38:39.984 --> 38:44.905
Well, didn't cost
anything, right?
Dreams are still free.

38:49.160 --> 38:51.162
♪♪

38:53.831 --> 38:57.126
(chatter on TV, indistinct)

39:08.054 --> 39:09.972
What's he doin'?

39:09.972 --> 39:15.519
He's just lying there
lookin' like he told himself
a joke in his sleep.

39:15.519 --> 39:18.189
(chuckles)
Yeah, I've seen that.

39:18.189 --> 39:21.609
Looks like he told it to himself
a couple times before too, and
he still thinks it's funny.

39:21.609 --> 39:23.778
(chuckles)

39:25.696 --> 39:28.824
-I'm worried about this girl.
-What girl?

39:28.824 --> 39:31.702
Russell.
She's not doin' good.

39:31.702 --> 39:36.582
-How do you tell?
-It's like she's...
stuck.

39:37.792 --> 39:40.878
About a week or so ago,
Bobby says she seems better,

39:40.878 --> 39:44.048
but it's like
it trailed off.

39:44.048 --> 39:48.386
Does "better" mean
ready to do what Bobby wants?

39:48.386 --> 39:53.099
He's not that way, Sylvia.
He loves her, but he's
concerned for her also.

39:58.354 --> 40:01.982
-Oh, there's another girl
with a problem.
-What?

40:05.152 --> 40:08.489
Andy, do you think that
we could really afford
me stopping work?

40:08.489 --> 40:10.616
Absolutely.

40:11.325 --> 40:14.412
I--I get a marshal's job
moonlighting. It won't
equal your income,

40:14.412 --> 40:16.789
but we'd have
less expenses.

40:16.789 --> 40:20.292
Yeah. We wouldn't need
a sitter for Theo or to budget
for my business clothes.

40:20.292 --> 40:22.711
-Don't you worry about money.
-Yeah. Right.

40:22.711 --> 40:26.549
No. I'm--I'm saying
it's manageable. I mean,
I never been afraid of work.

40:26.549 --> 40:30.761
We're--We're hip deep
in motions on
the Suarez case, and...

40:30.761 --> 40:33.055
Theo just keeps floatin'
into my head.

40:33.055 --> 40:38.310
I have to reconnect with what
I'm doing, just, kinda like
from a--a standing start.

40:38.310 --> 40:42.815
But then I'll wind up thinking,
"I'm doing this...

40:42.815 --> 40:48.904
"when I could be...
thinkin' about his dopey mug
without feeling guilty or...

40:48.904 --> 40:51.198
at home holding him."

40:56.620 --> 41:00.166
Does anybody have the right
to be that happy?

41:00.166 --> 41:02.209
Him and you...

41:03.752 --> 41:05.921
and me to help
where you could do it.

41:13.304 --> 41:15.306
♪♪

41:28.944 --> 41:31.780
-What's goin' on?
-Hi.

41:33.032 --> 41:35.451
-Ginger ale.
-Yeah.

41:40.247 --> 41:42.625
-You know about Jimmy.
-Yeah, I do.

41:42.625 --> 41:45.711
That was somethin', huh?

41:45.711 --> 41:48.339
That was awful.

41:48.339 --> 41:51.342
Yep.

41:51.342 --> 41:53.844
With Jimmy,
you never knew
what was comin' next.

41:58.057 --> 42:00.142
You know
what it was about?

42:02.520 --> 42:05.314
Jimmy didn't tell me
what he was into.

42:06.774 --> 42:09.985
I knew him a long time.
I never knew either.

42:09.985 --> 42:13.948
Hmm.
I'll believe that
if you want me to.

42:16.325 --> 42:18.285
You're the customer.

42:21.080 --> 42:24.583
Did Jimmy talk about me?

42:24.583 --> 42:29.588
He didn't need to say anything.
I could tell how fond he was.

42:31.966 --> 42:35.052
Did he tell you
if he slept with me?

42:35.052 --> 42:37.179
He didn't say.

42:39.974 --> 42:41.684
If he drugged me?

42:43.310 --> 42:47.189
No, babe.
That psycho snitch
didn't say.

42:47.189 --> 42:52.361
But I'll tell ya how
he had circulation problems
off bein' diabetic,

42:52.361 --> 42:57.491
and he did like to
add his little potions
to ladies' drinks.

42:57.491 --> 43:00.995
Girls half-knocked out
don't criticize
your performance.

43:03.872 --> 43:06.709
Am I taking you wrong?

43:09.295 --> 43:13.465
Are you lookin' to, uh,
find out if he drugged you,

43:13.465 --> 43:16.051
or did you wanna score
some more fizzies?

43:18.387 --> 43:19.388
What?

43:20.889 --> 43:26.061
Some girls like to get
somewhere without having
to say they wanna go.

43:26.061 --> 43:29.231
I didn't know
whether you had fun
with Jimmy or not.

43:32.109 --> 43:35.863
You think I wanted
that to happen--
for him to do that to me?

43:35.863 --> 43:39.158
-My mistake.
-You're lucky
I don't arrest you.

43:39.158 --> 43:41.827
Oh-ho, yeah.
Call the cops.

43:41.827 --> 43:46.707
Tell 'em a wacko skirt in
Patrick's wants me arrested for
asking what she's doing here.

43:48.876 --> 43:52.212
-I just need
to call a friend.
-I don't care who you call.

43:52.212 --> 43:54.798
Make it quick,
and get outta here!

44:00.262 --> 44:04.725
-(coin clinks
in pay phone)
-(tapping keys)

44:04.725 --> 44:06.310
(phone rings)

44:10.898 --> 44:12.941
-(ringing continues)
-(sighs)

44:12.941 --> 44:14.985
Yeah.

44:16.862 --> 44:20.074
All right.
I'll be right there.

44:20.074 --> 44:21.825
Get out then.

44:21.825 --> 44:27.081
I'll--I'll meet you
at, uh, that Sparta
or whatever that diner is.

44:27.081 --> 44:28.332
Who was that?

44:29.208 --> 44:31.293
Russell.

44:31.293 --> 44:35.923
-You were right.
-Yeah. Pin a rose on me.

44:45.182 --> 44:48.394
♪♪
